# Shadow Economy Detection & ZKP Community Bond
### AI-Assisted Immigrant Remittance Propensity Mapping | United States

[![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.12.7-blue)](https://python.org)
[![XGBoost](https://img.shields.io/badge/XGBoost-2.0.3-orange)](https://xgboost.readthedocs.io)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-green)](LICENSE)

## Overview

This repository contains the complete replication code for the paper:

> Khan, A. H. (2026). *Artificial Intelligence-Assisted Detection of Immigrant
> Remittance Propensity and a Novel Privacy-Preserving Bond for Domestic Capital
> Retention in the United States*. Journal of Business & Economic Studies.

The project addresses three research contributions:
1. An **XGBoost classifier** (ROC-AUC 0.876) that produces household-level
   remittance propensity scores from IPUMS ACS microdata
2. The **first PUMA-resolution map** of U.S. remittance outflows ($8.78B nationally)
3. A **ZKP Community Bond** simulation — a privacy-preserving federal savings
   instrument that retains $17.5M nationally in Year-1 at 6.7:1 government ROI

---

## Repository Structure

```
Shadow-Economy-ZKP-Bond/
|-- data_extraction.ipynb           # Script 1: Data cleaning & feature engineering
|-- XGBOOST_AI_model.ipynb          # Script 2: XGBoost model + PUMA outputs
|-- zkp_bond_simulation.ipynb       # Script 3: ZKP bond Monte Carlo simulation
|-- requirements.txt               # Python package dependencies
|-- figures/
|   |-- roc_curve.png              # Figure 1: ROC curve (AUC = 0.876)
|   |-- feature_importance.png     # Figure 2: XGBoost F-gain importance
|   |-- zkp_cost_benefit.png       # Figure 4: ZKP simulation results
|-- data/
|   |-- PUMA_REMITTANCE_SUMMARY.csv  # Aggregated PUMA-level remittance estimates
|   |-- ZKP_PUMA_IMPACT.csv          # Aggregated ZKP bond impact by PUMA
|-- README.md
```

---

## Data Source

This project uses **IPUMS USA American Community Survey (ACS) 5-year microdata**.

- Source: https://usa.ipums.org/usa/
- Citation: Ruggles, S., Flood, S., Sobek, M., et al. (2023). IPUMS USA: Version 13.0.
  Minneapolis, MN: IPUMS. https://doi.org/10.18128/D010.V13.0
- Access: **Free registration required.** Download is available at no cost.
- The raw microdata file (`raw_data.csv`) cannot be included in this repository
  due to IPUMS terms of use. Users must download it directly from IPUMS.

### How to Obtain the Data

1. Register at https://usa.ipums.org/usa/
2. Create an extract with the following variables:
   YEAR, SAMPLE, SERIAL, CBSERIAL, CLUSTER, STRATA, GQ, RELATE, RELATED,
   HHINCOME, INCWAGE, OWNCOST, RENTGRS, VEHICLES, AGE, CITIZEN, YRSUSA1,
   OCC, BPLD, STATEFIP, PUMA, HHWT, PERNUM, PERWT, COSTELEC, COSTGAS,
   COSTWATR, BPL
3. Select sample: 2018 ACS 5-year
4. Download as CSV and rename to `raw_data.csv`
5. Place in the same directory as the notebooks

---

## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/kamirhasan/Shadow-Economy-ZKP-Bond.git
cd Shadow-Economy-ZKP-Bond

# 2. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 3. Place raw_data.csv in the repo root (see Data Source above)

# 4. Run scripts in order:
#    Step 1: Data extraction
#    Step 2: XGBoost model
#    Step 3: ZKP simulation
# Open each notebook in Jupyter and run all cells sequentially.
```

---

## Running the Scripts

### Script 1: data_extraction.ipynb
- **Input:** raw_data.csv (881,743 rows)
- **Output:** MASTER_Remittance_V7.csv (351,893 records)
- **Runtime:** ~3 minutes
- **What it does:** Filters to household heads aged 18+ in standard GQ units,
  cleans IPUMS N/A codes, computes IS_SHADOW_ACTOR, estimates remittances

### Script 2: XGBOOST_AI_model.ipynb
- **Input:** MASTER_Remittance_V7.csv
- **Output:** MASTER_Remittance_V8_PREDICTIONS.csv, PUMA_REMITTANCE_SUMMARY.csv,
  ZKP_TARGET_HOUSEHOLDS.csv, roc_curve.png, remittance_feature_importance.png
- **Runtime:** 15–45 minutes (5-fold cross-validation is compute-intensive)
- **What it does:** Trains XGBoost + isotonic calibration, generates propensity
  scores, produces PUMA-level summaries

### Script 3: zkp_bond_simulation.ipynb
- **Input:** ZKP_TARGET_HOUSEHOLDS.csv
- **Output:** ZKP_BOND_SIMULATION_RESULTS.csv, ZKP_PUMA_IMPACT.csv,
  zkp_bond_cost_benefit.png
- **Runtime:** ~5 minutes
- **What it does:** Simulates ZKP bond adoption using 1,000 Monte Carlo iterations

---

## Key Results

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Sample size | 351,893 household heads |
| Origin communities | Mexico, India, Philippines, El Salvador, Bangladesh, Somalia |
| Model ROC-AUC | 0.876 (test set) / 0.875 ± 0.001 (5-fold CV) |
| Est. sample remittance | $2.04B/year |
| Est. national remittance | $8.78B/year |
| ZKP target households | 24,092 |
| Year-1 adopters (MC mean) | 2,727 ± 49 |
| Capital retained (national, Year-1) | $17.5M |
| Mature program (national, 35%) | $48.7M/year |
| Government ROI | 6.7:1 |

